The paper deals with fair division of goods, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The problem involves maximizing a social welfare function, which is a common objective in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
